United Bank for Africa Gains Most in 2 Weeks on Profit Forecast

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-09-13T11:40:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/united-bank-for-africa-gains-most-in-2-weeks-on-profit-forecast.html
United Bank for Africa Plc (UBA) , a
Nigerian lender with operations in 19 African countries, rose
the most in more than two weeks after saying it expects profit
of 14.5 billion naira ($94 million) in the fourth quarter.  The stock gained 12 kobo, or 3 percent, to 4 naira by 11:30
a.m. in Lagos, the biggest intraday advance since Aug. 25.  Revenue will be 176 billion naira, while profit before tax
will be 18 billion naira, the Lagos-based bank said in a
statement posted on the website of the  Nigerian Stock Exchange 
yesterday. It didnâ€™t provide comparative figures.  To contact the reporter on this story:
